 government), Japanese baths in San Francisco-and a little bit about Chaucer too. Ultimately, Huerta sketches out habits of living while thinking that allow us to consider what it means to live with and try to peer beyond history even as we are caught up in the middle of it.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCultural pluralismzIllinoiszChicago. 0aDecolonizationxStudy and teaching (Higher). 0aEthnic restaurantszIllinoiszChicago. 0aEthnicity. 0aFeminist criticism. 0aFood habitsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aMexican American cookingxSocial aspects. 0aMexican AmericansxEthnic identity. 0aMexican AmericanszIllinoiszChicagovBiography. 0aMexican AmericanszIllinoiszChicago. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Cultural, Ethnic & Regional / Hispanic & Latino.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478021483zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021483423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021483/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles